'''San Borja''' was a Spanish mission established in 1762 by the   at the  settlement of Adac, west of .
Before becoming a mission, the future site of San Borja served as a ''visita'' or subordinate mission station for . The construction of buildings was begun in 1759. A stone church was completed during the  period, in 1801.
The mission was abandoned in 1818, as the native population in this part of the peninsula disappeared. Structures and ruins survive.